a.xlink:title: Return all divisors of x in sorted order.
Finds x such that a^x = b (mod M) using baby-step giant-step algorithm. a and M must be coprime.
Returns the composition of permutations a and b, so that ret[i] = a[b[i]].
Return whether integer n >= 2 is prime.
Returns a primitive root modulo M.
Returns the cycle decomposition of the permutation.
Returns the totient of the integer n.
